Los Cuates isn't a spot you gravitate to while in Adams Morgan. Yelp will steer you to better-rated restaurants nearby. While their tacos aren't noteworthy, Los Cuates does shine in a few areas:  1) Outdoor seating: They have an open-air yet covered patio seating with powerful heaters that actually keep you warm.  2) Service: They are kind and responsive.  3) Margs: Their pitchers of their OG margarita is a good way to start the weekend after a long week.  4) Queso: The cheaper the queso, the better. Their yellow queso is so good and comes with warm chips.

Do NOT get delivery/takeout from this place. The food is nasty and the packaging is absolutely terrible. This photo is their nacho platter and chicken enchiladas as they arrived. As you can see, just revolting. They also screwed up basic parts of our order (e.g. giving us refried instead of black beans), but that's small potatoes next to how absolutely inedible this food was. I'm not super picky when it comes to tex mex but this is hands down the worst I've gotten in DC. Really, really bad. Go with one of the many alternatives in town.

No seasoning, the beans were undercooked and grainy, they were also watery like someone was trying to make them in a hurry and was trying to cheat the creamy texture. And what does this place have against salt?  Everything else was just ok. Edible, but not particularly good. But the beans were so bad I'm leaving a 1 star review instead of 3.
